        "action": "Revise legislation on sulphite allergy so all products state the presence.",
        "additional_details": "https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/food-allergy/causes/\r\n\r\nhttps://www.anaphylaxis.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Sulphites-2019.pdf\r\n\r\nhttps://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/j.1365-2222.2009.03362.x\r\n\r\nhttps://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/j.1365-2222.2010.03528.x",
        "background": "At the moment only products with 10mg/kg need to declare the presence of sulphites. Individuals react to levels lower than this,  with an asthma attack, which is a life threatening condition. Given that individuals with this allergy have life threatening responses the legislation should be changed.",
